message.content: One of the most significant events that happened in Monaco in the past 5 years was the wedding of Prince Albert II of Monaco and Charlene Wittstock on July 1 and 2, 2011. The wedding was a highly anticipated event and attracted worldwide attention. It was a lavish affair, with various ceremonies and celebrations taking place over the course of two days. The wedding was seen as a significant moment for the principality, as it marked the union of the reigning prince and the former South African Olympic swimmer.
